Metrorail had to suspend all services due to ongoing vandalism and the death of one of their security guards. CAPE TOWN - Trains on Metrorail's central line in Cape Town resumed on Wednesday morning. Metrorail had to suspend all services due to ongoing vandalism and the death of one of their security guards. More than 60% of the province's passengers travel on the central line. Acting group CEO of Prasa Cromet Molepo says they will work around the clock to ensure all trains run on time. “If we continue to work the way we have through crisis, I stand confident that we will only get better.” Trains will run on an hourly basis up until 8pm on Wednesday. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)